metadata.name: Provence #423
metadata.description:
The south of France namely the Provence has a cultural history of being an inspiration for impressionists and post-impressionists in the past.
For me personally the Provence is the place i was spending long, peaceful holidays as a child within beautiful nature.
This work does not so much aim for being realistic, rather than give an impression or feeling for this wonderful landscape. 
There are just a few different elements and concepts and yet there is variety of fascinating results.
I really hope you will enjoy your minting.

Notes:
STARTUP AND RENDERING MAY TAKE SOME TIME. (Up to 1min)
Code was written in typescript.
The only used libraries were chroma.js and simplex-noise

metadata.description:

THE FEARZ UNIVERSE

metadata.name: It came from the stars #23
metadata.description:
"It is said that long ago, the Greater Will sent a golden star bearing a beast into the Lands Between ..."

Fully procedural beast and environment, everything generated at runtime.
A love letter to FromSoftware.

Don't hesitate to use the camera controls to view the beasts.

More informations on the generator's origins and how it is made available at : https://ulucode.com/wp/it-came-from-the-stars/

Controls:
Press space to open/close a menu.
Mouse Left   : Rotate
Mouse Right  : Pan
Mouse Middle : Dolly/zoom

Capture & Exports :
Export size depends on your browser window size. Choose a multiplier and press the button. If the capture doesn't work, try a smaller multiplier.

Warning: This piece is GPU intensive, it may not render on lower end devices. Chrome very recommended

Additional controls:
Press "a" to alternate between different anti-aliasing intensity. Warning : GPU intensive
Press "s" to check some stats

Menu font is EB Garamond
Powered by three.js
NFT License

metadata.name: Ersbla #743
metadata.description:
Ersbla is part of the fxhash live minting experience at Proof of People, London 2022. 

It is the third entry in a series of abstract generative experiments inspired by the graphic and textile work of Anni and Josef Albers. As a follow-up to the 'Sabler' and 'Lebras' collections, 'Ersbla' produces textile effects using a combination of thousands of tiny dots arranged on variable grids, resulting in a wide variety of unique Bauhaus-inspired compositions in a variety of palettes.

Press 'S' to save a high-resolution 2400 x 3396 px image in PNG format.

Depending on the density of your output, please allow up to a few seconds for your edition to generate.

metadata.name: Galarith #46
metadata.description:
Galarith is a study of emergence and sacred geometry. Unashamedly born of Scythe and set in the world of Galarith which is my daughter's home brew D&D campaign plus a splattering of my own Gods. The symbols are a representation of offerings to the Gods who see over the world of Galarith.

Minimal colour palettes allow the project as a whole to sit cohesively together. Deploying a mixture of blend modes lets the colours layer and at times gives a sepia effect. While attributes are assigned, they are for the purpose of filtering the collection. The "In Honor Of" trait is broken down into 9 sets of fixed rotation values and one random rotation and represents the Gods of Galarith. "Loxy" being the wildcard of the deity's.

Traits:
4 Banner Colours
3 Clans
10 Gods

Made in P5.js

Press "s" to save .png image

Please contact Zero Alpha if you wish to obtain a high-resolution image of your token. @ZeroAlpha_NZ
